## Specs-D11 Core Flows Document Format
**Status:** implemented
**Module:** `specs/auto-forge/flows.ad`
**Tags:** stack:both
**Depends on:** Specs-G13, Specs-A2

### Purpose

`flows.ad` provides a **horizontal perspective** on the system: it describes execution flows that cross module boundaries. This complements the **vertical perspective** of module-based specs ( Goals → Architecture → Designs within a single module).

### Document Structure

```markdown
# Core Flows

## Flow-N: {Flow Name}
**Modules involved**: {comma-separated module list}
**Entry**: {what triggers this flow}
**Exit**: {what marks completion}

### Overview
{Brief description of the flow}

### Sequence Diagram
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant A
    participant B
    A->>B: message
```

### Key Steps

#### Step N: {Step Name}
**Trigger**: {when this step executes}
**Processing**: {what happens}
**Data Flow**: {input} → {processing} → {output}

### Related Specs
- `Module-A1` — links to architecture decisions
- `Module-D3` — links to design specs
```

### Flow Catalog

| Flow ID | Name | Modules | Span |
|---------|------|---------|------|
| Flow-1 | Forge Chat Loop | chat, provider, runtime, relay | User message → SSE response |
| Flow-2 | Relay Pipeline Execution | relay, provider, runtime, specs, chat | FlowSpec → Completed/Failed |
| Flow-3 | Agent Turn Execution | agent-config, provider, runtime, relay | Agent spawn → Handoff document |
| Flow-4 | Spec Document Lifecycle | specs, forge | Read → Edit → Derive → Persist |
| Flow-5 | Gate Approval Flow | relay, chat, ui-system | Gate trigger → User decision → Resume |

### Conventions

- Every flow MUST have a Mermaid `sequenceDiagram`
- Every step MUST document Trigger, Processing, and Data Flow
- Every flow MUST link to related spec IDs at the bottom
- Flows do NOT replace module specs; they reference them
- Flow IDs use `Flow-N` format (not tied to module prefix)

### Relationship to Module Specs

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "Vertical: Module Specs"
        MG[relay/goals.ad]
        MA[relay/architecture.ad]
        MD[relay/designs.ad]
    end

    subgraph "Horizontal: Flows"
        F1[Flow-1 Chat Loop]
        F2[Flow-2 Relay Pipeline]
    end

    F1 --> MA
    F1 --> MD
    F2 --> MA
    F2 --> MD
```

- Module specs answer **"what is this component and how does it work?"**
- Flow specs answer **"how does data move through the system?"**

